narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This is a required course for the Literature major, so I would recommend this course to any Lit major (obviously), and also people interested in reading texts from nonfamiliar cultural genres.
This class is wonderful and consistently thought-provoking. I'm tempted to add some kind of tagline here ("Take this, and never see Romeo and Juliet the same way again!"). (It's true.)
Good general literature class. Fair amount of reading but papers aren't too bad at all
I would recommend it to any student interested in literature.
I would take it if you're a lit major; otherwise, I'd pass.
